body.description: To claim that the SwissGear 7272 27-Inch Energie hard luggage collection is simply durable would be an understatement. Equipped with a rugged PC shell, our hardside suitcase displays a polished architect. Our hard-case suitcase also features eight multi-directional spinner wheels for 360-degree maneuverability. Adding to its symmetric aesthetic, its main compartment opens into a split case that features a tie-down clothing compartment with a zippered accessory pocket, while the other side houses a large zippered compartment with additional mesh and cinched pockets. Finished with a retractable locking handle, our hard suitcase expands for additional packing space and features an integrated TSA-approved lock for extra security. Pack right utilizing the luxury fixtures ingrained within this sleek spinner luggage case.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome carry-on case
reviews.reviewText: It is so rigid, great looking, plenty of space, excellent wheels to move around airport 360 degrees rotation with awesome ride, TSA lock is excellent. I will give it 10 stars if I could. Delivery was perfect, package was well protected. Excellent seller. I will most certainly recommend this to anyone.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 1, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this luggage
reviews.reviewText: Purchased mainly for business trips mixed with some pleasure. Friends of ours have an older Swiss set of luggage that is durable, a nice look, with great storage. After much research, I went with my first hard shelled piece the 27” and love it! The wheels are the best I’ve ever had, smooth, tilt well when pulling behind, and strolls well nicely beside you. I love the dimensional look of this luggage, giving it a bit of a pop. The inside has ample storage and many pockets. The lock combination is easy to change and has held up well. After reading previous reviews on Swiss website and on here, I would say my only complaint so far, is the same as another, the handle on top could raise a bit higher if you are stacking luggage. I have the Swiss backpack and that does sit well on it. I don’t think I’ll ever buy a fabric again. I love the design, look, storage, and durability.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality looks good
reviews.reviewText: Really good quality, as I expect from Swiss Gear. Zipper compartments are well thought out and I had plenty of room for warm clothes and my full size tempurpedic pillow I always take with me. I used a set of packing cubes too, just regular ones not vacuum bags. The only thing that was not clear about the charge cable; you need to use your own mini power supply. There’s a clever internal pocket and a rubber sealed grommet to run the usb cable built in. I have a power pack about the size of my phone. It adds a few ounces and slips in the pocket they designed for this purpose. A good hard sided case - I’d recommend! I’d buy the bigger one too!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 5, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good case, but arrived dirty and used
reviews.reviewText: I have both the carry-on version and the 24" checked version. After a lifetime of mis-matched luggage it was time to have a nice set! I like that these have the 8 wheels instead of just the 4 for durability. I like the built in TSA lock. I also like the interior storage that comes built-in with these cases; which is helpful if you're moving from location to location frequently during a vacation. I expect that the carry-on version will last a very long time, but I'm not sure about the checked one. There is no grab handle for the base and the case itself isn't light. You won't want to overload the 24"+ sizes or it's going to get damaged.My main complaint is that the case arrived filthy from sitting in a dirty warehouse. It also arrived slightly "used" from someone who chose to return it. People, if you are going to return an item, put it back the way you received it. Someone else is likely going to get your "used" item in the condition you returned it. Failure to do so means that the karma gods are going to make the wheels fall off you luggage from henceforth.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good set of luggage
reviews.reviewText: This luggage set is awesome and I recommend it for a frequent travels. The wheels on the luggage makes you feel you’re driving a rolls Royce. Very smooth gliding through the airport, no noise. Very spacious and you can fit anything in it .

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Everything I Wanted and Needed
reviews.reviewText: This luggage is great for carry on for airplane. Well made and durable. Lightweight with a hard exterior. I loved the number lock on the zippers. The wheels glided super smooth through airport and city pavements. I thought I ordered grey and came olive green which I liked even more. The best part I needed this purchase to come in asap for my vacation and came sooner than expected. Worth the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great luggage for carry on!
reviews.reviewText: We needed new luggage for an upcoming trip to Greece and bought 2 of these as it complied with the size restrictions. We were able to pack 10 days of clothes and toiletries in these bags to avoid checking luggage for this trip. The wheel are great and the light-weight nature of the luggage made it easier to stow in the overhead compartment of the airlines.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 20, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Telescopic handles bike twice
reviews.reviewText: Bought my first carry on worked great for about 4 months. I absolutely loved the design and the ease of the rolling feature. I travel frequently 3-4 times a month.The telescoping handle broke at the grip. The warranty support was awesome took pictures. Weird I had to cut the tag out but I guess so much fraud happening.Got the replacement with a store credit within i few days. Fantastic support.Used the replacement 10 times the telescoping handle broke at the grip again. Needless to say I won’t do three strikes.Please fix the telescoping handle and the curve of the grip so it holds up and grip doesn’t dig into your hand as you push through the airport.Fix that and I’ll try again. Most Swiss products outlive most of their usefulness. Not this one.Pic#1 bag #2 pic #2 bag #1
